Reasoning: The paper deals with fault-tolerance in nanoscale algorithmic self-assembly, which involves the use of abstract Tile Assembly Models (aTAM) and the aggregation of square "tiles" constructed from DNA. This falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the use of O(log n) unique tile types to assemble an n x n square, which involves numerical analysis (cs.NA) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper proposes a construction that prevents errors due to insufficient attachment, which involves control systems (cs.SY).
